<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>

<p>The <b>Advisory AI Ideas</b> application is an enterprise Power Apps Canvas App that provides KPMG Advisory with a centralised platform for capturing, assessing, prioritising, and tracking AI use-case ideas, alongside a curated library of reusable AI prompts. The application replaces a prior React/TypeScript single-page application and has been rebuilt natively on the Microsoft Power Platform to leverage Dataverse as the data layer, enabling seamless integration with Microsoft 365, Teams, and Power Automate workflows.</p>

<p>The application serves two core functions:</p>
<ol>
    <li><b>AI Ideas Pipeline</b> &mdash; A structured workflow for employees to submit AI use-case ideas, have them assessed against a weighted value/feasibility framework, and track them through an 11-stage lifecycle pipeline from ideation to scaling.</li>
    <li><b>AI Prompt Library</b> &mdash; A searchable, filterable catalogue of vetted AI prompts across six categories, with rating, usage tracking, community submission, and an admin review queue.</li>
</ol>

<div class="callout">
<b>Key Business Value:</b> Enables KPMG Advisory to systematically identify, evaluate, and prioritise the highest-impact AI opportunities while equipping staff with best-practice AI prompts to improve productivity across all business functions.
</div>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 2. PROJECT BACKGROUND & OBJECTIVES -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>2. Project Background &amp; Objectives</h2>

<h3>2.1 Background</h3>
<p>KPMG Advisory recognised the need for a structured approach to managing the growing volume of AI use-case ideas generated across business functions. An initial prototype was developed as a React/TypeScript web application using browser localStorage for data persistence. To achieve enterprise-grade data management, governance, and integration with the existing Microsoft 365 ecosystem, the application was migrated to Microsoft Power Apps Canvas App backed by Dataverse.</p>

<h3>2.2 Business Objectives</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>#</th><th>Objective</th><th>Success Metric</th></tr>
<tr><td>OBJ-01</td><td>Provide a single entry point for all AI use-case ideas across the firm</td><td>100% of new AI ideas submitted through the platform</td></tr>
<tr><td>OBJ-02</td><td>Enable objective, quantitative prioritisation of AI initiatives</td><td>All submitted ideas scored using the weighted value/feasibility framework</td></tr>
<tr><td>OBJ-03</td><td>Provide full lifecycle visibility from ideation to scaling</td><td>Pipeline dashboard reflects real-time status of all ideas</td></tr>
<tr><td>OBJ-04</td><td>Establish a curated, reusable prompt library to boost AI adoption</td><td>Prompt library used at least 500 times per month within 3 months</td></tr>
<tr><td>OBJ-05</td><td>Ensure enterprise governance, security, and auditability</td><td>All data stored in Dataverse with role-based access control enforced</td></tr>
<tr><td>OBJ-06</td><td>Integrate with Microsoft 365 ecosystem (Teams, Outlook, Power Automate)</td><td>App accessible via Teams; automated notifications for key events</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 3. STAKEHOLDERS & ROLES -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>3. Stakeholders &amp; Roles</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>Role</th><th>Description</th><th>Key Responsibilities</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Submitter</b> (All Staff)</td><td>Any KPMG Advisory employee across all business functions</td><td>Submit AI use-case ideas; submit new prompts; browse &amp; rate prompts; copy prompts for use</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Assessor</b></td><td>Senior staff or AI leads responsible for evaluating ideas</td><td>Score ideas across value &amp; feasibility dimensions; submit assessments; update idea status in pipeline</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Admin / Reviewer</b></td><td>Platform administrators and prompt review committee</td><td>Approve/reject submitted prompts; manage pipeline statuses; configure security roles; access all analytics</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Leadership</b></td><td>Partners and directors overseeing AI strategy</td><td>View analytics dashboards; review prioritised ideas; make investment decisions</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 4. SCOPE -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>4. Scope</h2>

<h3>4.1 In Scope</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Module</th><th>Capabilities</th></tr>
<tr>
    <td><b>Ideas Pipeline</b></td>
    <td>
        <ul>
            <li>Idea submission form (title, description, AI capability area, business function, expected benefits, submitter info)</li>
            <li>Ideas dashboard with search, status filter, and business function filter</li>
            <li>Idea detail view with full information display</li>
            <li>Assessment panel with 7 scoring dropdowns, live score calculation, and quadrant determination</li>
            <li>Pipeline board view showing ideas across all 11 lifecycle stages</li>
            <li>Drag-and-drop (or dropdown-based) status transitions between pipeline stages</li>
            <li>Ideas analytics dashboard (by status, quadrant, business function, AI capability area)</li>
        </ul>
    </td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td><b>Prompt Library</b></td>
    <td>
        <ul>
            <li>Searchable, filterable prompt catalogue (by category, complexity, keyword)</li>
            <li>Prompt detail view with full text, metadata, and copy-to-clipboard functionality</li>
            <li>Star-based rating system (1&ndash;5) with optional text feedback</li>
            <li>Usage count tracking (incremented on copy)</li>
            <li>Prompt submission form for community contributions</li>
            <li>Admin review queue with approve/reject workflow</li>
            <li>Prompt analytics dashboard (category distribution, top prompts, ratings)</li>
        </ul>
    </td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td><b>Platform</b></td>
    <td>
        <ul>
            <li>Dataverse tables for structured data storage</li>
            <li>Role-based access control (Submitter, Assessor, Admin)</li>
            <li>Global navigation header across all screens</li>
            <li>KPMG-branded theme (colour palette, typography)</li>
            <li>Power Automate flows for notifications and approval workflows</li>
        </ul>
    </td>
</tr>
</table>

<h3>4.2 Out of Scope</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Direct integration with external AI services (e.g., calling OpenAI/Azure OpenAI APIs from within the app)</li>
    <li>Financial budgeting or resource allocation for ideas</li>
    <li>Custom AI model training or deployment</li>
    <li>Multi-language / internationalisation support</li>
    <li>Mobile-specific responsive layout (app is optimised for tablet/desktop at 1366 &times; 768)</li>
    <li>Advanced priority-matrix scatter-chart visualisation (future enhancement)</li>
</ul>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 5. FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS — IDEAS MODULE -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>5. Functional Requirements &mdash; Ideas Module</h2>

<h3>FR-100: Idea Submission</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>ID</th><th>Requirement</th><th>Priority</th></tr>
<tr><td>FR-101</td><td>The system shall provide a form for users to submit a new AI use-case idea with the following fields: <b>Title</b> (text, required, max 200 chars), <b>Description</b> (multi-line text, required), <b>AI Capability Area</b> (choice, required), <b>Business Function</b> (choice, required), <b>Expected Benefits</b> (multi-line text, optional), <b>Submitter Name</b> (auto-populated from logged-in user or manual entry), <b>Submitter Email</b> (auto-populated or manual entry).</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-102</td><td>Upon submission, the system shall create a new record in the <code>AI Ideas</code> Dataverse table with Status defaulting to <b>"Submitted"</b> and Created Date set to the current timestamp.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-103</td><td>The system shall generate a unique Idea ID automatically (Dataverse auto-number or GUID).</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-104</td><td>The system shall display a success notification upon successful submission and reset the form.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-105</td><td>The system shall validate that all required fields are populated before allowing submission.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>FR-200: Ideas Dashboard</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>ID</th><th>Requirement</th><th>Priority</th></tr>
<tr><td>FR-201</td><td>The system shall display all ideas in a scrollable gallery, sorted by creation date (newest first).</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-202</td><td>Each idea card in the gallery shall display: <b>Title</b>, <b>AI Capability Area</b>, <b>Business Function</b>, <b>Status badge</b> (colour-coded), and <b>Created Date</b>.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-203</td><td>The system shall provide a <b>text search</b> control that filters ideas by Title, AI Capability Area, or Business Function.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-204</td><td>The system shall provide a <b>Status filter</b> dropdown with options: All, Submitted, Screening, Assessment, Prioritized, Development, Pilot, Deployed, Scaling, On Hold, Rejected, Archived.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-205</td><td>The system shall provide a <b>Business Function filter</b> dropdown with options: All, Audit, Tax, Advisory, Deal Advisory, IT, Operations, Human Resources, Finance, Marketing, Legal, Risk &amp; Compliance.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-206</td><td>All three filters (search, status, business function) shall work in combination (AND logic).</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-207</td><td>Selecting an idea from the gallery shall navigate to the Idea Detail screen with the selected idea's data loaded.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>FR-300: Idea Detail &amp; Assessment</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>ID</th><th>Requirement</th><th>Priority</th></tr>
<tr><td>FR-301</td><td>The system shall display the full details of the selected idea: Title, Description, AI Capability Area, Business Function, Expected Benefits, Submitter Name, Submitter Email, Status, and Created Date.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-302</td><td>The system shall display the idea's current Status as a colour-coded badge.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-303</td><td>The system shall provide an <b>Assessment Panel</b> with 7 dropdown controls for scoring dimensions: Business Growth, Cost Efficiency, Business Resilience, Business Agility, Technical Feasibility, Internal Readiness, External Readiness. Each dropdown shall offer choices: Low, Medium, High.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-304</td><td>The system shall <b>calculate Value Score and Feasibility Score in real time</b> as the user selects dropdown values, using the weighted scoring formula defined in Section 7 (Business Rules).</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-305</td><td>The system shall <b>determine and display the Quadrant</b> (Likely Wins, Calculated Risks, Marginal Gains, Avoid) in real time based on the calculated scores.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-306</td><td>The system shall provide a <b>"Submit Assessment"</b> button that writes the 7 dimension values, Value Score, Feasibility Score, Quadrant, Assessed By (current user), and Assessed Date to the <code>AI Idea Assessments</code> table and updates the idea's status to "Prioritized".</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-307</td><td>The system shall display visual score bars or indicators showing the Value Score and Feasibility Score relative to the maximum possible score (3.0).</td><td>Should</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-308</td><td>If an assessment already exists for the idea, the system shall display the existing scores and quadrant (read-only or editable based on role).</td><td>Should</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>FR-400: Pipeline Board</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>ID</th><th>Requirement</th><th>Priority</th></tr>
<tr><td>FR-401</td><td>The system shall display a <b>Kanban-style pipeline board</b> with one column per active lifecycle stage: Submitted, Screening, Assessment, Prioritized, Development, Pilot, Deployed, Scaling.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-402</td><td>Each column shall display a header with the stage name and a count of ideas in that stage.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-403</td><td>Each idea card in the pipeline shall show the Title and a Status dropdown allowing the user to move the idea to a different stage.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-404</td><td>Changing the status dropdown shall immediately update the idea's Status in the <code>AI Ideas</code> Dataverse table via a Patch operation.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-405</td><td>The pipeline view shall exclude ideas with terminal statuses (On Hold, Rejected, Archived) from the main board columns.</td><td>Should</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>FR-500: Ideas Analytics</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>ID</th><th>Requirement</th><th>Priority</th></tr>
<tr><td>FR-501</td><td>The system shall display summary KPI cards: <b>Total Ideas</b>, <b>Assessed Ideas</b>, <b>Likely Wins count</b>, <b>Average Value Score</b>.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-502</td><td>The system shall display a <b>column chart</b> showing the distribution of ideas by Status.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-503</td><td>The system shall display a <b>pie chart</b> showing the distribution of assessed ideas by Quadrant.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-504</td><td>The system shall display a <b>bar chart</b> showing the distribution of ideas by Business Function.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-505</td><td>The system shall display a <b>bar chart</b> showing the distribution of ideas by AI Capability Area.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
</table>

