<!-- 6. FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS — PROMPT LIBRARY MODULE -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>6. Functional Requirements &mdash; Prompt Library Module</h2>

<h3>FR-600: Prompt Library Browse &amp; Search</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>ID</th><th>Requirement</th><th>Priority</th></tr>
<tr><td>FR-601</td><td>The system shall display all <b>Approved</b> prompts in a searchable, scrollable gallery.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-602</td><td>Each prompt card shall display: <b>Title</b>, <b>Category badge</b> (colour-coded), <b>Rating</b> (numeric or stars), <b>Usage Count</b>, and <b>Complexity Level</b>.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-603</td><td>The system shall provide a <b>text search</b> control that filters prompts by Title, Prompt Text, or Tags.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-604</td><td>The system shall provide a <b>Category filter</b> dropdown with options: All, Client Deliverables, Internal Productivity, Research &amp; Analysis, Data &amp; Finance, Creative &amp; Marketing, Technical.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-605</td><td>The system shall provide a <b>Complexity filter</b> dropdown with options: All, Beginner, Intermediate, Expert.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-606</td><td>All filters shall work in combination (AND logic).</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-607</td><td>Selecting a prompt from the gallery shall navigate to the Prompt Detail screen.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>FR-700: Prompt Detail &amp; Interaction</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>ID</th><th>Requirement</th><th>Priority</th></tr>
<tr><td>FR-701</td><td>The system shall display the full prompt record: Title, Category, Prompt Text, Output Format, Complexity Level, Best Practices, Owner, Tags, AI Tools, Version, Usage Count, Rating, and Status.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-702</td><td>The system shall provide a <b>"Copy to Clipboard"</b> button that copies the Prompt Text to the user's clipboard and increments the Usage Count by 1 in Dataverse.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-703</td><td>The system shall display a confirmation notification upon successful copy.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-704</td><td>The system shall provide a <b>5-star rating widget</b> (5 clickable star icons) allowing the user to rate the prompt from 1 to 5.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-705</td><td>The system shall provide a <b>text input</b> for optional rating feedback.</td><td>Should</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-706</td><td>The system shall provide a <b>"Submit Rating"</b> button that creates a new record in the <code>AI Prompt Ratings</code> table and updates the prompt's running average rating and rating count.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>FR-800: Prompt Submission</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>ID</th><th>Requirement</th><th>Priority</th></tr>
<tr><td>FR-801</td><td>The system shall provide a form for users to submit a new prompt with the following fields: <b>Title</b> (text, required), <b>Prompt Text</b> (multi-line text, required), <b>Category</b> (choice, required), <b>Output Format</b> (choice, required), <b>Complexity Level</b> (choice, required), <b>Best Practices</b> (multi-line text, optional), <b>Owner</b> (text, optional), <b>Tags</b> (text, semicolon-separated, optional), <b>AI Tools</b> (multi-select choice, optional).</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-802</td><td>Upon submission, the system shall create a new record in the <code>AI Prompts</code> table with Status defaulting to <b>"Pending"</b>, Version "1.0.0", Usage Count 0, Rating 0, and Rating Count 0.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-803</td><td>The system shall display a success notification and reset the form after submission.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>FR-900: Admin Review Queue</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>ID</th><th>Requirement</th><th>Priority</th></tr>
<tr><td>FR-901</td><td>The system shall display a gallery of all prompts with Status = <b>"Pending"</b>.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-902</td><td>Each item in the review queue shall display the Title, Category, Owner/Submitter, and Prompt Text preview.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-903</td><td>Each item shall have an <b>"Approve"</b> button that updates the prompt's Status to "Approved".</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-904</td><td>Each item shall have a <b>"Reject"</b> button that updates the prompt's Status to "Rejected".</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-905</td><td>The review queue shall only be accessible to users with the Admin role.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>FR-1000: Prompt Analytics</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>ID</th><th>Requirement</th><th>Priority</th></tr>
<tr><td>FR-1001</td><td>The system shall display summary KPI cards: <b>Total Prompts</b>, <b>Total Copies</b> (sum of Usage Count), <b>Average Rating</b>, <b>Total Ratings</b>.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-1002</td><td>The system shall display a chart showing the distribution of prompts by Category.</td><td>Must</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-1003</td><td>The system shall display a ranked list of Top Prompts by Usage Count.</td><td>Should</td></tr>
<tr><td>FR-1004</td><td>The system shall display a chart showing the distribution of prompts by Complexity Level.</td><td>Should</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 7. BUSINESS RULES & SCORING LOGIC -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>7. Business Rules &amp; Scoring Logic</h2>

<h3>7.1 Score Mapping</h3>
<p>All seven assessment dimensions use a three-level ordinal scale mapped to numeric values:</p>
<table>
<tr><th>Choice Label</th><th>Numeric Value</th></tr>
<tr><td>Low</td><td>1</td></tr>
<tr><td>Medium</td><td>2</td></tr>
<tr><td>High</td><td>3</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>7.2 Value Score Calculation</h3>
<p>The Value Score is a weighted average of four business-value dimensions. The score ranges from 1.0 (all Low) to 3.0 (all High).</p>

<div class="callout-purple">
<b>Value Score</b> = (Business Growth &times; <b>0.20</b>) + (Cost Efficiency &times; <b>0.20</b>) + (Business Resilience &times; <b>0.30</b>) + (Business Agility &times; <b>0.30</b>)
</div>

<table>
<tr><th>Dimension</th><th>Weight</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>Business Growth</td><td>0.20 (20%)</td><td>Potential to support market expansion, new products/services, and customer experience enhancements</td></tr>
<tr><td>Cost &amp; Operational Efficiency</td><td>0.20 (20%)</td><td>Potential to realise cost optimisation, process automation, and reduced activity times across business and IT</td></tr>
<tr><td>Business Resilience</td><td>0.30 (30%)</td><td>Potential to enable organisational and IT resilience, cyber security, and regulatory compliance</td></tr>
<tr><td>Business Agility</td><td>0.30 (30%)</td><td>Potential to adapt, transform, and execute at pace in response to changes in strategy and opportunities</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>7.3 Feasibility Score Calculation</h3>
<p>The Feasibility Score is a weighted average of three implementation-readiness dimensions. The score ranges from 1.0 (all Low) to 3.0 (all High).</p>

<div class="callout-purple">
<b>Feasibility Score</b> = (Technical Feasibility &times; <b>0.50</b>) + (Internal Readiness &times; <b>0.30</b>) + (External Readiness &times; <b>0.20</b>)
</div>

<table>
<tr><th>Dimension</th><th>Weight</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>Technical Feasibility</td><td>0.50 (50%)</td><td>Maturity and availability of AI capabilities, infrastructure, and integration technologies</td></tr>
<tr><td>Internal Readiness</td><td>0.30 (30%)</td><td>Organisational AI literacy, data readiness, and willingness to adopt AI-driven solutions</td></tr>
<tr><td>External Readiness</td><td>0.20 (20%)</td><td>Alignment with legal, regulatory requirements, and market/vendor ecosystem maturity</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>7.4 Quadrant Determination</h3>
<p>Ideas are classified into one of four strategic quadrants based on a threshold of <b>2.0</b> applied to both scores:</p>

<table>
<tr><th>Quadrant</th><th>Condition</th><th>Strategic Interpretation</th><th>Colour</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Likely Wins</b></td><td>Value &ge; 2.0 <b>AND</b> Feasibility &ge; 2.0</td><td>High value with high feasibility &mdash; prioritise these for immediate investment</td><td style="background-color:#28A745; color:white;">#28A745</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Calculated Risks</b></td><td>Value &ge; 2.0 <b>AND</b> Feasibility &lt; 2.0</td><td>High value but low feasibility &mdash; strategic bets requiring de-risking</td><td style="background-color:#FFC107; color:black;">#FFC107</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Marginal Gains</b></td><td>Value &lt; 2.0 <b>AND</b> Feasibility &ge; 2.0</td><td>Easy to implement but limited business impact &mdash; pursue only if low effort</td><td style="background-color:#17A2B8; color:white;">#17A2B8</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Avoid</b></td><td>Value &lt; 2.0 <b>AND</b> Feasibility &lt; 2.0</td><td>Low value and hard to implement &mdash; deprioritise</td><td style="background-color:#DC3545; color:white;">#DC3545</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>7.5 Rounding</h3>
<p>Scores are rounded to <b>1 decimal place</b> for display using <code>Round(score, 1)</code> in Power Fx. The quadrant determination uses the rounded value.</p>

<h3>7.6 Idea Lifecycle Stages</h3>
<p>Each idea progresses through a defined 11-stage lifecycle. The first 8 stages form the active pipeline; the final 3 are terminal states:</p>
<table>
<tr><th>Order</th><th>Stage</th><th>Badge Colour</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>1</td><td>Submitted</td><td style="background-color:#6C757D; color:white;">#6C757D</td><td>Raw idea captured, awaiting initial review</td></tr>
<tr><td>2</td><td>Screening</td><td style="background-color:#17A2B8; color:white;">#17A2B8</td><td>Initial review for strategic alignment and viability</td></tr>
<tr><td>3</td><td>Assessment</td><td style="background-color:#483698; color:white;">#483698</td><td>Detailed value and feasibility scoring in progress</td></tr>
<tr><td>4</td><td>Prioritized</td><td style="background-color:#00A3A1; color:white;">#00A3A1</td><td>Ranked and selected for implementation</td></tr>
<tr><td>5</td><td>Development</td><td style="background-color:#FFC107; color:black;">#FFC107</td><td>Building MVP or prototype solution</td></tr>
<tr><td>6</td><td>Pilot</td><td style="background-color:#FF6B35; color:white;">#FF6B35</td><td>Testing with limited users to validate</td></tr>
<tr><td>7</td><td>Deployed</td><td style="background-color:#28A745; color:white;">#28A745</td><td>Full production rollout complete</td></tr>
<tr><td>8</td><td>Scaling</td><td style="background-color:#00338D; color:white;">#00338D</td><td>Optimisation and organisational expansion</td></tr>
<tr><td>&mdash;</td><td>On Hold</td><td style="background-color:#ADB5BD; color:black;">#ADB5BD</td><td>Paused due to resources or timing</td></tr>
<tr><td>&mdash;</td><td>Rejected</td><td style="background-color:#DC3545; color:white;">#DC3545</td><td>Did not pass a stage gate</td></tr>
<tr><td>&mdash;</td><td>Archived</td><td style="background-color:#343A40; color:white;">#343A40</td><td>Completed lifecycle or deprecated</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>7.7 Prompt Lifecycle States</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Status</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>Draft</td><td>Prompt is being authored (not yet submitted)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Pending</td><td>Submitted for review; visible only in the admin review queue</td></tr>
<tr><td>Approved</td><td>Reviewed and approved; visible in the public prompt library</td></tr>
<tr><td>Rejected</td><td>Reviewed and rejected; not visible in the library</td></tr>
<tr><td>Archived</td><td>Previously approved but now retired from active use</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>7.8 Rating Calculation</h3>
<p>When a user submits a rating, the prompt's running average and count are updated:</p>
<div class="callout">
<b>New Average</b> = ((Current Rating &times; Rating Count) + New Rating) / (Rating Count + 1)<br/>
<b>New Count</b> = Rating Count + 1
</div>

