<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 10. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>10. Non-Functional Requirements</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>ID</th><th>Category</th><th>Requirement</th></tr>
<tr><td>NFR-01</td><td>Performance</td><td>Screens shall load within 3 seconds on a standard corporate network. Gallery filtering shall respond within 1 second.</td></tr>
<tr><td>NFR-02</td><td>Availability</td><td>The application shall be available during standard business hours (99.5% uptime), aligned with the Microsoft Power Platform SLA.</td></tr>
<tr><td>NFR-03</td><td>Scalability</td><td>The application shall support up to 500 concurrent users and store up to 10,000 idea records and 5,000 prompt records without performance degradation.</td></tr>
<tr><td>NFR-04</td><td>Usability</td><td>The application shall be usable by non-technical staff with no training. UI elements shall follow standard Power Apps conventions and KPMG brand guidelines.</td></tr>
<tr><td>NFR-05</td><td>Data Retention</td><td>All data shall be retained in Dataverse indefinitely. Archived records shall remain accessible for audit purposes.</td></tr>
<tr><td>NFR-06</td><td>Compatibility</td><td>The application shall function in Microsoft Edge and Google Chrome (latest versions). It shall also be accessible via the Power Apps mobile app on iOS and Android (tablet form factor).</td></tr>
<tr><td>NFR-07</td><td>Accessibility</td><td>The application should follow WCAG 2.1 Level AA guidelines where feasible within Power Apps Canvas App constraints.</td></tr>
<tr><td>NFR-08</td><td>Maintainability</td><td>All Dataverse tables, columns, and app screens shall use descriptive naming conventions. Formulas shall include comments for complex logic.</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 11. INTEGRATION & AUTOMATION REQUIREMENTS -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>11. Integration &amp; Automation Requirements</h2>

<h3>11.1 Power Automate Flows</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Flow Name</th><th>Trigger</th><th>Actions</th><th>Priority</th></tr>
<tr>
    <td><b>New Idea Notification</b></td>
    <td>When a row is added to <code>AI Ideas</code></td>
    <td>
        <ol>
            <li>Send confirmation email to submitter</li>
            <li>Post notification to Teams review channel</li>
            <li>Update idea status from Submitted &rarr; Screening</li>
        </ol>
    </td>
    <td>Should</td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td><b>Prompt Approval Workflow</b></td>
    <td>When a row is added/modified in <code>AI Prompts</code> with Status = Pending</td>
    <td>
        <ol>
            <li>Start approval request to designated reviewer(s)</li>
            <li>If approved: Update status to Approved &rarr; notify submitter</li>
            <li>If rejected: Update status to Rejected &rarr; notify submitter with feedback</li>
        </ol>
    </td>
    <td>Should</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h3>11.2 Microsoft 365 Integration</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Integration</th><th>Description</th><th>Priority</th></tr>
<tr><td>Microsoft Teams</td><td>App pinned as a Teams tab; notifications posted to designated channels</td><td>Should</td></tr>
<tr><td>Outlook</td><td>Email notifications triggered by Power Automate for idea submissions and prompt approvals</td><td>Should</td></tr>
<tr><td>Azure AD / Entra ID</td><td>User authentication and identity via Azure AD SSO (inherited from Power Platform)</td><td>Must</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 12. SECURITY & ACCESS CONTROL -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>12. Security &amp; Access Control</h2>

<h3>12.1 Authentication</h3>
<p>Users authenticate via <b>Azure Active Directory (Entra ID)</b> single sign-on, inherited from the Power Platform environment. No separate login is required.</p>

<h3>12.2 Role-Based Access Control</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Role</th><th>AI Ideas</th><th>AI Idea Assessments</th><th>AI Prompts</th><th>AI Prompt Ratings</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Submitter</b></td><td>Create, Read (own + all)</td><td>Read</td><td>Read (Approved only), Create (Status defaults to Pending)</td><td>Create, Read</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Assessor</b></td><td>Create, Read, Update (status)</td><td>Create, Read, Update</td><td>Read, Create</td><td>Create, Read</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Admin</b></td><td>Full CRUD</td><td>Full CRUD</td><td>Full CRUD (incl. Approve/Reject)</td><td>Full CRUD</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>12.3 Data Security</h3>
<ul>
    <li>All data at rest is encrypted by Dataverse (Microsoft-managed encryption)</li>
    <li>All data in transit is encrypted via TLS 1.2+</li>
    <li>Dataverse audit logging is enabled for all tables to track create/update/delete operations</li>
    <li>Environment-level DLP (Data Loss Prevention) policies apply to the app's connectors</li>
</ul>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 13. ASSUMPTIONS & CONSTRAINTS -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>13. Assumptions &amp; Constraints</h2>

<h3>13.1 Assumptions</h3>
<ol>
    <li>All users have Microsoft 365 E3/E5 licenses with Power Apps included.</li>
    <li>A Dataverse environment has been provisioned and is accessible to the development team.</li>
    <li>Users have standard corporate network access to make.powerapps.com and the Power Apps runtime.</li>
    <li>The KPMG brand guidelines and colour codes used in this document are approved for internal application use.</li>
    <li>The weighted scoring framework (weights, thresholds, quadrant definitions) has been agreed upon by Advisory leadership and is not subject to change during initial rollout.</li>
    <li>The Prompt Library categories and AI Tools list may evolve over time; the Choice columns in Dataverse can be extended by an Admin without code changes.</li>
</ol>

<h3>13.2 Constraints</h3>
<ol>
    <li><b>Platform:</b> The application is built as a Power Apps Canvas App and is subject to the platform's delegation limits (default 2,000 rows), control library, and formula language capabilities.</li>
    <li><b>Layout:</b> Canvas Apps have fixed-layout design; responsive behaviour across drastically different screen sizes is limited.</li>
    <li><b>Offline:</b> The application requires an active network connection to read/write Dataverse data. No offline mode is supported in the initial release.</li>
    <li><b>Delegation:</b> Certain filter operations (e.g., <code>in</code> operator for search) are non-delegable. For datasets exceeding 2,000 rows, additional optimisation (e.g., Dataverse views, indexed columns) may be required.</li>
    <li><b>Concurrent Editing:</b> Dataverse uses last-write-wins for record updates. No explicit record locking or conflict resolution is implemented.</li>
</ol>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 14. ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>14. Acceptance Criteria</h2>

<h3>14.1 Ideas Module</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>ID</th><th>Criterion</th></tr>
<tr><td>AC-01</td><td>A user can submit a new idea with all required fields, and it appears in the Ideas Dashboard with Status = "Submitted".</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-02</td><td>The Ideas Dashboard correctly filters ideas by search text, status, and business function (individually and in combination).</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-03</td><td>Selecting an idea navigates to the detail screen showing all idea fields.</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-04</td><td>An assessor can select Low/Medium/High for all 7 dimensions and see the Value Score, Feasibility Score, and Quadrant update in real time.</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-05</td><td>Given inputs of Business Growth = Medium, Cost Efficiency = High, Business Resilience = High, Business Agility = High, the Value Score displays <b>2.8</b>.</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-06</td><td>Given inputs of Technical Feasibility = High, Internal Readiness = High, External Readiness = Medium, the Feasibility Score displays <b>2.8</b>.</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-07</td><td>Given Value Score &ge; 2 and Feasibility Score &ge; 2, the Quadrant displays "Likely Wins".</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-08</td><td>Submitting an assessment creates a record in AI Idea Assessments and updates the idea's status to "Prioritized".</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-09</td><td>The Pipeline board displays ideas in the correct status columns, and changing status via dropdown immediately updates the record.</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-10</td><td>The Ideas Analytics screen displays accurate counts and charts reflecting current data.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>14.2 Prompt Library Module</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>ID</th><th>Criterion</th></tr>
<tr><td>AC-11</td><td>The Prompt Library displays only Approved prompts, correctly filtered by search, category, and complexity.</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-12</td><td>Clicking "Copy to Clipboard" copies the Prompt Text and increments the Usage Count by 1.</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-13</td><td>A user can rate a prompt (1&ndash;5 stars), and the prompt's running average and count update correctly.</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-14</td><td>A user can submit a new prompt, and it appears in the Review Queue with Status = "Pending".</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-15</td><td>An Admin can approve or reject a pending prompt, and the status updates accordingly.</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-16</td><td>The Prompt Analytics screen displays accurate KPIs and charts.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>14.3 Platform</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>ID</th><th>Criterion</th></tr>
<tr><td>AC-17</td><td>The global navigation header appears on all 10 screens and correctly navigates between them.</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-18</td><td>The app can be accessed from Microsoft Teams as a pinned tab.</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-19</td><td>Role-based access control restricts the Review Queue to Admin users only.</td></tr>
<tr><td>AC-20</td><td>The app loads within 3 seconds on a standard corporate network.</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 15. GLOSSARY -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>15. Glossary</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>Term</th><th>Definition</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>BRD</b></td><td>Business Requirements Document &mdash; a formal document describing the business needs and expectations for a system.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Canvas App</b></td><td>A type of Power Apps application where the maker has full control over the layout, design, and formula logic of every screen and control.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Dataverse</b></td><td>Microsoft's cloud-native data platform built on Azure SQL, providing structured data storage, role-based security, and business logic for Power Platform applications.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Delegation</b></td><td>The process by which Power Apps pushes filter/sort operations to the data source (Dataverse) rather than processing locally. Non-delegable operations are limited to the first 2,000 rows.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Power Fx</b></td><td>The low-code formula language used in Power Apps Canvas Apps, inspired by Excel formulas.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Power Automate</b></td><td>Microsoft's workflow automation platform for creating automated business processes (flows).</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Quadrant</b></td><td>A classification of an assessed AI idea based on its Value Score and Feasibility Score relative to the 2.0 threshold.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Value Score</b></td><td>A weighted composite score (1.0&ndash;3.0) measuring the business value potential of an AI idea across four dimensions.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Feasibility Score</b></td><td>A weighted composite score (1.0&ndash;3.0) measuring the implementation readiness of an AI idea across three dimensions.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Pipeline</b></td><td>The 11-stage lifecycle through which an AI idea progresses from initial submission to scaling or archival.</td></tr>
</table>

